-- Qatar National Bank to Grow in Syria, Oman, Sudan; Doesn't Plan Bond Sale
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-07-08T06:19:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/qatar-national-bank-to-expand-in-syria-oman-sudan-plans-no-bond-sale.html

          
          
             Qatar National Bank SAQ, the Persian
Gulf countryâ€™s biggest bank by assets, plans to increase its
branch network in Syria, Oman and Sudan, Chief Executive Officer
Shareef Al Emadi told a news conference in Doha today.  
 The bank will open four new branches in Oman, 15 in Syria
and five in Sudan this year, he said. The bank has three
branches in Syria, one in Oman and one in Sudan now, he said.
The bank has no immediate plans to sell bonds, he said.  
